quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  30,20,"Of His signs is that He created you from dust, then, behold, you are humans scattering [all over]"
  30,21,"And of His signs is that He created for you mates from your own selves that you may take comfort in them, and He ordained affection and mercy between you. There are indeed signs in that for a people who reflect"
  30,22,"Among His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the difference of your languages and colours. There are indeed signs in that for those who know"
  30,23,"And of His signs is your sleep by night and day, and your pursuit of His bounty. There are indeed signs in that for a people who listen"
  30,24,"And of His signs is that He shows you the lightning, arousing fear and hope, and He sends down water from the sky, and with it revives the earth after its death. There are indeed signs in that for people who exercise their reason"
  30,25,"And of His signs is that the sky and the earth stand by His command, and then, when He calls you forth from the earth, behold, you will come forth"
  30,26,To Him belongs whoever is in the heavens and the earth. All are obedient to Him
  30,27,"It is He who originates the creation, and then He will bring it back—and that is more simple for Him. His is the loftiest description in the heavens and the earth, and He is the All-mighty, the All-wise"